<item>
            <title>[FLINK-31288] Disable overdraft buffer for batch shuffle</title>
                <link>https://issues.apache.org/jira/browse/FLINK-31288</link>
                <project id="12315522" key="FLINK">Flink</project>
                    <description>&lt;p&gt;Only pipelined / pipelined-bounded partition needs overdraft buffer. More specifically, there is no reason to request more buffers for non-pipelined (i.e. batch) shuffle. The reasons are as follows:&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;ol&gt;
	&lt;li&gt;For BoundedBlockingShuffle, each full buffer will be directly released.&lt;/li&gt;
	&lt;li&gt;For SortMergeShuffle, the maximum capacity of buffer pool is 4 * numSubpartitions. It is efficient enough to spill this part of memory to disk.&lt;/li&gt;
	&lt;li&gt;For Hybrid Shuffle, the buffer pool is unbounded. If it can&apos;t get a normal buffer, it also can&apos;t get an overdraft buffer.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ol&gt;
</description>
